{
  "texts": [
    "Observation 5.",
    "Including the URL as metadata (whether prepended or appended), enhances the model's latent grasp of writing style and overall document quality.",
    "In this work, we show that LLM pretraining can be accelerated by conditioning on a wider range of metadata, extending beyond the commonly used URL.",
    "Our experiments indicate that fine-grained metadata-such as fine-grained quality scores and domain information-consistently yields stronger improvements than coarse-grained alternatives when prepended.",
    "Appending metadata as auxiliary prediction tasks can accelerate training as well."
  ]
}